pull_request.title: Update dependency web3-shh to v1.2.5
pull_request.body:
This PR contains the following updates:

| Package | Type | Update | Change |
|---|---|---|---|
| [web3-shh](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js) | dependencies | patch | [`1.2.4` -> `1.2.5`](https://renovatebot.com/diffs/npm/web3-shh/1.2.4/1.2.5) |

---

### Release Notes

<details>
<summary>ethereum/web3.js</summary>

### [`v1.2.5`](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md#​125)

[Compare Source](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/compare/v1.2.4...v1.2.5)

##### Added

-   `eth_requestAccounts` as `requestAccounts` added to web3-eth package ([#​3219](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3219))
-   `sha3Raw` and `soliditySha3Raw` added to web3-utils package ([#​3226](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3226))
-   `eth_getProof` as `getProof` added to web3-eth package ([#​3220](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3220))
-   `BN` and `BigNumber` objects are now supported by the `abi.encodeParameter(s)` method ([#​3238](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3238))
-   `getPendingTransactions` added to web3-eth package ([#​3239](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3239))
-   Revert instruction handling added which can get activated with the `handleRevert` module property ([#​3248](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3248))
-   The `receipt` does now exist as property on the error object for transaction related errors ([#​3259](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3259))
-   `internalType` added to `AbiInput` TS interface in `web3-utils` ([#​3279](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3279))
-   Agent option added to the `HttpProvider` options ([#​2980](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/2980))

##### Changed

-   `eth-lib` dependency updated (0.2.7 => ^0.2.8) ([#​3242](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3242))

##### Fixed

-   Fix crash when decoding events with identical signatures, differently indexed args ([#​3272](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3272))
-   Fix user supplied callback not fired in eth.accounts.signTransaction ([#​3283](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3283))
-   Fix minified bundle ([#​3256](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3256))
-   `defaultBlock` property handling fixed ([#​3247](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3247))
-   `clearSubscriptions` does no longer throw an error if no running subscriptions do exist ([#​3246](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3246))
-   callback type definition for `Accounts.signTransaction` fixed ([#​3280](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3280))
-   fix: export bloom functions on the index.js
-   Prefer receipt status to code availability on contract deployment ([#​3298](https://togithub.com/ethereum/web3.js/issues/3298))

</details>

---
